Herring landed at Ardglass week ending  28th June 1890: 920 Mease. Price per Mease: 18s to 32s 6d. Highest number of boats fishing on one day: Scotch 48, Irish 22, Manx 0.(according Freeman's July 3rd).

OED Mease: &quot;A measure of herrings (formerly also occas. of other fish), usually equal to five hundreds (esp. long hundreds); a container holding this.&quot; 
Long hundred: &quot;great or long hundred  , usually = six score, or a hundred and twenty.&quot;
